description.narrative:
Scope of work of TAO-Pilipinas, Inc.
1. Conduct an orientation workshop and provide technical inputs and advice to CCI and CERD staff
and volunteers on disaster-resilient site planning and shelter design;
2. Develop training module for local carpenters on disaster-resilient site planning and shelter design
in CCI areas;
3. Develop basic visual orientation materials (powerpoint presentations and handouts) containing
principles and key messages on disaster-resilient site planning and shelter design for the use of
CCI in community orientation processes;
4. Conduct a technical training on disaster-resilient site planning and shelter design for local
carpenters in the four CCI-assisted municipalities (20-30 participants per municipality) with
hands-on application;
5. Document technical assistance provided by TAO-Pilipinas and prepare a project report containing
an evaluation of the project outputs and lessons gained from the experience;
